text: The Bennington component makes up 85 percent of the map unit. Slopes are 0 to 2 percent. This component is on ground moraines on till plains. The parent material consists of Wisconsin loamy till derived from sandstone and shale. Depth to a root restrictive layer is greater than 60 inches. The natural drainage class is somewhat poorly drained.  Water movement in the most restrictive layer is moderately low.  Available water to a depth of 60 inches (or restricted depth) is moderate.  Shrink-swell potential is moderate. This soil is not flooded. It is not ponded. A seasonal zone of water saturation is at 9 inches during January, February, March, April, May, November, December. Organic matter content in the surface horizon is about 3 percent.  Nonirrigated land capability classification is 2w.  This soil does not meet hydric criteria.
